So it's not perfectly drawn but this is a

00:00:06.520 --> 00:00:09.920
reasonable attempt at a square, and of course

00:00:09.920 --> 00:00:11.720
one of the things that we know about a square

00:00:11.720 --> 00:00:15.020
is all of the sides are going to have the same length.

00:00:15.020 --> 00:00:17.090
So if the length of this side is x,

00:00:17.090 --> 00:00:19.050
well all of them are going to have,

00:00:19.050 --> 00:00:21.490
all of them are going to have length x.

00:00:21.490 --> 00:00:24.490
We also know this is a, these are going to be

00:00:24.490 --> 00:00:27.110
right angles, that's what makes it a square.

00:00:27.110 --> 00:00:29.190
Now the question I want to ask,

00:00:29.190 --> 00:00:31.390
are the lengths of the side of a square

00:00:31.390 --> 00:00:33.890
proportional to its area?

00:00:33.890 --> 00:00:35.450
And I encourage you to pause the video and think about it,

00:00:35.450 --> 00:00:37.890
are the lengths of a side, are the lengths

00:00:37.890 --> 00:00:42.180
of the sides of a square proportional to the square's area?

00:00:43.370 --> 00:00:45.250
Well to think about that let's draw,

00:00:45.250 --> 00:00:46.750
let's have a little table here.

