So side length, side length

00:00:52.210 --> 00:00:55.450
and that's going to be given as x,

00:00:55.450 --> 00:00:58.290
so that's going to be x, and then

00:00:58.290 --> 00:00:59.850
I'll have another column, I can draw

00:00:59.850 --> 00:01:02.150
that a little bit neater so let me

00:01:02.150 --> 00:01:04.520
use this tool, so there you go,

00:01:04.520 --> 00:01:07.490
and I'm going to make two columns,

00:01:07.490 --> 00:01:09.881
two columns right over here,

00:01:09.881 --> 00:01:12.170
and then over here I'm going to put area.

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:15.750
Area, and what's the area going to be?

00:01:15.750 --> 00:01:19.090
Well the area is going to be one of the sides squared,

00:01:19.090 --> 00:01:21.800
I suppose you could view it as the width times the height,

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:25.650
so its going to be x times x or x squared.

00:01:25.650 --> 00:01:27.490
So let's just pick some values for x

00:01:27.490 --> 00:01:29.850
and then figure out what the area is going to be.

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.790
So if x is going to be equal to one,

00:01:32.790 --> 00:01:34.550
the area's going to be one times one,

00:01:34.550 --> 00:01:36.020
which is still one.

00:01:36.020 --> 00:01:38.590
If x is going to be equal to two,

00:01:38.590 --> 00:01:40.780
the area's going to be two times two,

00:01:40.780 --> 00:01:42.790
which is equal to four.

00:01:42.790 --> 00:01:44.920
If x is going to be equal to three,

00:01:44.920 --> 00:01:47.770
the area's going to be three times three,

00:01:47.770 --> 00:01:51.430
which is equal to nine, and I could keep going

00:01:51.430 --> 00:01:53.190
but I think this is enough, these are enough points

00:01:53.190 --> 00:01:56.450
to think about is the side length proportional to the area,

00:01:56.450 --> 00:01:58.590
or is the area proportional to the side length?

00:01:58.590 --> 00:01:59.890
Now one of the ways you can think about

00:01:59.890 --> 00:02:02.840
proportionality is, are the ratios between

00:02:02.840 --> 00:02:05.050
the side length and the corresponding area

00:02:05.050 --> 00:02:07.650
always the same, so we want to look at

00:02:07.650 --> 00:02:10.250
the ratio between side length and area,

00:02:10.250 --> 00:02:13.160
or area and side length, as long as they're always constant.

